We recommended that Management:

(23) Strictly comply with Section 68 of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA 9184 as reiterated under Annex D, Section 3.1 of the same IRR on the imposition of liquidated damages due to late deliveries of the procured goods and services;

(24) Ensure that date of receipt of goods/services be indicated in the Delivery Receipt and that date of acceptance and inspection be indicated in the AIR;

(25) Ensure collection/recovery of the liquidated damages and cost of undelivered items from the concerned supplier through: a) reduction of the amounts due them in other projects/contracts; and b) send collection letter; 

(26) Strictly comply with Section 62.1 of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA 9184 in the deduction of retention money from the payment of goods procured thru public bidding; and

(27) Submit the Property Acknowledgment Receipt (PAR) for the procured rescue and disaster-related equipment to establish accountability for the properties.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:
To conduct risk assessment;
To identify critical processes and functions;
To determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation;
To conduct risk analysis and impact analysis;
To formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and
To submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.
Further, we recommended that members of the working group be capacitated by allowing them to attend seminars/trainings on the formulation of the PSCP.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require:

(11) The Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Road Network System;

(12) The Acting Supply/Property Officer to continue rendering a report on Local Road Network at the end of the accounting period, to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete LRNPCs for all roads and its components;

(13) The Acting Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects to be implemented during his incumbency and to exert extra effort in determining the cost of the road components of road projects implemented in prior years based on available documents;

 (14) The Municipal Accountant to keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and reconcile the same with the LRNPCs and the result of the physical inventory taking at the end of each year; and the Municipal Accountant to include the necessary disclosure on the total road network system of the LGU in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant to identify and establish the correct balance of the remaining Due to LGUs for each source agency and thereafter:   

(17) Return to the concerned source agencies the unutilized balance of the fund transfer wherein the agreement requires the return thereof;

(18) Revert to the Unappropriated Surplus the balances of fund transfers in the nature of financial assistance and subsidy wherein the agreement does not mention of the disposition of the unused balance and that future utilization thereof will be subject to the usual accounting, auditing and budgeting laws, rules and regulations; 


(19) Retain special purpose funds; and  

(20) Clean the books of accounts, particularly the account Due to LGUs, in accordance with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2016-005 in order to present fairly the Liability accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that Management:

(42) Strictly comply with the submission of copies of Purchase Orders and Notices of Deliveries within the reglementary period in accordance with COA Circular Nos. 2009-001 and 96-010;

(43) Ensure completeness of the required supporting documents as well as of signatures in the SDs for all Contracts/POs submitted to COA for review in accordance with COA Circular Nos. 2012-001 and 2009-001; 

