We recommended and Management agreed to direct:

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC), particularly the BAC Secretariat to document the transactions and/or events as it transpired during the different phases of the procurement process to support its validity and propriety; 
The GSO or concerned Department or Officials to impose strictly the terms and conditions, particularly on the posting of performance bonds and delivery dates, in such a way that performance bond are posted upon award prior to the execution of the Contract/PO, and see to it that procured items are delivered on time, otherwise imposed liquidated damages for late deliveries; 
The Municipal Accountant to strengthen the processing/pre-audit activities, as part of the Agency’s overall accounting and internal control system, to avoid control overrides, and ensure that transactions being processed, paid and recorded are duly approved and supported with complete documentation and/or technical requirements. The use of Checklist provided for under the Revised Documentary Requirements for Common Government Transactions prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and the Revised RIRR of R.A. No. 9184 may prove useful as guide in the processing of claims for payment; and 
The BAC, GSO and Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking supporting documents, data and/or information for our review, as listed in Annex A,  otherwise the related transactions may be suspended or disallowed in audit.

We recommended that Management require: 
The OIC-Municipal Assessor to hasten the updating of the Assessment Roll  and furnish the Municipal Treasurer of the same, in order for him to update the RPTAR Index Card as basis for the preparation of the certified list and to serve as an ideal and verifiable benchmark of performance in their tax collection efficiency;
The OIC-Municipal Treasurer to also update his RPTAR Index Card,  compute for the tax due and furnish the Municipal Accountant’s Office with a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV)  to record the debit to Real Property Tax Receivable/Special Education Tax Receivable and crediting Deferred Real Property Tax Income and Deferred Special  Education Tax Income, based on the certified list furnished by the Municipal Treasurer, pursuant to the said manual; and 
The OIC-Municipal Assessor to follow up the Schedule of Market Values pending for approval at the Sangguniang Panlalawigan.

We recommend that the Accounting Department to:

Maintain a Special Account for the 80% Share from Energy Sources in the General Fund and prepare separate financial statements pertaining thereto pursuant to the abovementioned rules and regulations and;  

Keep and maintain complete subsidiary records for the 80% Share from Energy Sources to provide accurate information/details of the general ledger balances of this special account to assist/aid management in making decisions for the proper disposition and utilization of the same.
